      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, framing the Due Process Clause as a vital, living safeguard is an excellent pedagogical approach. It allows students to see the Constitution not as a static document, but as a dynamic framework capable of adapting to modern societal needs. This perspective emphasizes that the amendment's purpose is to ensure meaningful liberty, pushing the legal system toward greater protection for marginalized groups. This view promotes the idea that the law should actively advance justice, not just maintain the status quo.",
      "source": "target",
